#compdef linx-server
# =============================================================================
# linx-server — Andrei Marcu's "Self-hosted file/code/media
#               sharing website" — a Go HTTP server for
#               hosting an "uploadify-style" file-sharing
#               service.  Users upload files via web UI or
#               API; receive shareable URLs; configurable
#               expiry; supports text/code sharing with
#               syntax highlighting + Markdown rendering;
#               S3 backend optional.  Powers the popular
#               linx.li service since 2015.
#               Distinguishing from transfer.sh, 0x0.st,
#               file.io, ffsend, and other file-share
#               services by:
#                 - HTTP HANDLER + UI in one binary — single
#                   `linx-server` binary serves both the
#                   upload API + the web UI; no separate
#                   frontend deployment
#                 - PONGO2 (Django/Jinja2) TEMPLATES — UI
#                   pages rendered via pongo2 templates;
#                   Django-style {% block %} / {% extends %}
#                   inheritance for theming
#                 - 30+ COMMAND-LINE FLAGS via Go stdlib flag
#                   package — all via INI-flags integration
#                   (vharitonsky/iniflags) so command-line
#                   flags + .ini config files share the same
#                   names
#                 - STORAGE BACKEND CHOICE — local filesystem
#                   (default) OR S3-compatible (--s3-endpoint /
#                   --s3-region / --s3-bucket); supports MinIO,
#                   Wasabi, Backblaze B2 + AWS S3
#                 - META STORAGE BACKEND — separate metadata
#                   storage (delete keys, MIME types, expiry)
#                   alongside file storage
#                 - EXPIRY ENFORCEMENT — files auto-deleted
#                   after configurable expiry; --cleanup-every-
#                   minutes controls cleanup interval; --max-
#                   expiry caps user-requested expiry
#                 - SHA256 INTEGRITY via minio/sha256-simd —
#                   uploaded files SHA256-hashed for content-
#                   addressing + de-duplication
#                 - CONTENT SECURITY POLICY — HARDCODED CSP
#                   for the upload page + separate CSP for
#                   file-serving (prevents XSS via uploaded
#                   HTML / SVG)
#                 - REFERRER POLICY — separate policies for UI
#                   + file responses (privacy-conscious
#                   defaults)
#                 - X-FRAME-OPTIONS — SAMEORIGIN by default
#                   (prevents clickjacking)
#                 - BLACKFRIDAY MARKDOWN — uploaded .md files
#                   rendered to HTML via russross/blackfriday
#                   + microcosm-cc/bluemonday sanitizer
#                 - MIMETYPE DETECTION via gabriel-vasile/
#                   mimetype — automatic MIME-type sniffing of
#                   uploads
#                 - BASIC AUTH via --basicauth + --authfile —
#                   restrict upload access; --remoteauthfile
#                   for API-key auth
#                 - GOJI WEB FRAMEWORK — zenazn/goji for
#                   routing + middleware (graceful shutdown,
#                   request ID, real-IP)
#                 - FASTCGI MODE via --fastcgi — run behind
#                   nginx / apache as FastCGI backend
#                 - REMOTE UPLOADS via --remoteuploads — fetch
#                   a URL server-side + store as upload
#                 - CUSTOM PAGES via --custompagespath —
#                   serve user-authored Markdown pages
#                 - BENCODE SUPPORT via zeebo/bencode — .torrent
#                   file parsing (lists tracked files)
#                 - GO.RICE EMBEDDED ASSETS — static assets
#                   (CSS, JS, fonts) embedded in binary via
#                   GeertJohan/go.rice
#               Used by: privacy-conscious file-share operators
#               replacing centralized services (transfer.sh,
#               0x0.st), homelab admins running shared
#               infrastructure, and as a reference
#               implementation of pongo2 + Goji + AWS SDK +
#               sha256-simd + bencode + bluemonday + Goji
#               composition in Go.
