#
# WHAT IS pongo2 AND WHY IS IT THE 76TH Go CLI LIBRARY?
#
# pongo2 is the canonical Django/Jinja2-style template engine
# for Go.  Distinct from Go's stdlib text/template + html/
# template (which have Go-specific syntax not compatible with
# Django/Jinja2/Liquid/Twig/Nunjucks tradition) and from the
# newer templ (a-h/templ, typed compile-time Go templates).
#
# Five distinguishing characteristics from tera (R673):
#
#   1. SAME JINJA2 SYNTAX, DIFFERENT LANGUAGE — pongo2 and
#      tera share the Django/Jinja2 syntax family:
#         {{ variable }}                interpolation
#         {{ variable | filter }}       filter
#         {{ variable | filter:arg }}   parameterized filter (pongo2)
#         {{ variable | filter(arg) }}  parameterized filter (tera)
#         {% if %} / {% endif %}        conditional
#         {% for x in xs %} / {% endfor %} iteration
#         {% block name %} / {% endblock %} inheritance
#         {% extends "base" %}          extension
#         {% include "partial" %}       inclusion
#      tera + pongo2 differ in subtle places (filter argument
#      syntax `:arg` vs `(arg)`, fn calls in templates) but
#      90% portable.
#
#   2. REFLECTION-BASED CONTEXT LOOKUP — pongo2 resolves
#      `{{ a.b.c }}` via Go reflection: tries map[string],
#      then struct field, then method.  Same algorithm as
#      Jinja2 but using Go's reflect package.  tera uses serde
#      Serialize trait.
#
#   3. AUTO-ESCAPE BY DEFAULT — HTML autoescaping built-in;
#      `{{ user_input }}` is HTML-escaped automatically;
#      `{{ trusted_html | safe }}` opts out.  tera also has
#      auto-escape (controlled by `autoescape` option +
#      `| safe` filter).
#
#   4. ~50 BUILT-IN DJANGO FILTERS — including Django-specific
#      filters: timesince, timeuntil, pluralize, slugify,
#      truncatewords_html, urlize, wordcount, wordwrap,
#      stringformat.  tera has ~60 filters with overlapping
#      coverage.
#
#   5. FLORIAN-SCHLACHTER / flosch ECOSYSTEM PROVENANCE —
#      distinct from Vincent Prouillet (Keats/tera).  Florian
#      is German; Vincent is French.  Both maintain Jinja2-
#      family template engines in their respective ecosystems.
#
